<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B1AFFD6FD65F615FA82F463" pageId="4" pageNumber="515" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B1AFFD6FD65F615FCE6F508" blockId="4.[753,1347,2660,3086]" pageId="4" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis id="E3ED26401B1AFFD6FD65F615FC1CF559" bold="true" box="[753,908,2660,2693]" pageId="4" pageNumber="515">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B1AFFD6FC0BF615FAAAF559" authority="Thomas, 1902" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1902" box="[927,1338,2660,2693]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="515" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frater">Ctenomys frater Thomas, 1902</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="61F1F00F1B1AFFD6FD66F6FAFCE6F508" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798388335" pageId="4" pageNumber="515">“Potosi,” Bolivia, 19°35&quot; 8, 65°45&quot; W, c.4300 m.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D126FA521B1AFFD6FD61F6A8FA82F463" blockId="4.[753,1347,2660,3086]" pageId="4" pageNumber="515">
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B1AFFD6FD61F6A8FC52F526" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1902" box="[757,962,2777,2810]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="515" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frater">Ctenomys frater</taxonomicName>
was initially classified in the Bolivian-Paraguayan group but is in the fraterspecies group based on mtDNA. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 52 and FN = 78 (mordosus), and sperm is simple symmetric. Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
